@startuml parallel-quicksort-game-flow
!theme plain
!include ../shared/theme.puml
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #F0F8FF

title Performing Parallel Quicksort with the Existing Tool

|#LightBlue| Coordinator |
|#LightGreen| All Players in Sub-Group |
|#LightYellow| System |

|System|
start
:Generate **n** shuffled cards\nin shared container;
:Initialize recursion stack\nwith full array [0..n-1]\nand all **p** players;

|Coordinator|
partition "**Phase 1 — Pivot Selection**" {
    :Select pivot card\n(median-of-three or random);
    note right
      Pivot card highlighted
      with glowing border.
      ——
      **Maps to:** pivot selection
      strategy in quicksort
    end note
    :Confirm pivot →\nshow partition zones;
}

|All Players in Sub-Group|
partition "**Phase 2 — Collaborative Partition**" {
    :Left zone ← cards ≤ pivot\nRight zone ← cards > pivot;
    note left
      All players move
      cards simultaneously.
      Pivot marker divides
      the container.
      ——
      **Maps to:** parallel
      partitioning step
    end note
    :Players rearrange cards\naround the pivot;
}

|System|
:Validate partition correctness;
note right
  Check: all cards left
  of pivot ≤ pivot value,
  all cards right > pivot
end note

if (Partition balanced?) then (roughly equal)
    :Assign ~p/2 players\nto each sub-array;
    note right: **Balanced load**
else (highly unequal)
    :More players assigned\nto larger sub-array;
    note right
      **Load imbalance!**
      Visual warning shown.
      ——
      **Maps to:** poor pivot
      → uneven workload
    end note
endif

partition "**Phase 3 — Recursive Fork**" {
    fork
        |Coordinator|
        partition "Left Sub-Array" #Lavender {
            if (Size > 1?) then (yes)
                :Sub-group repeats\nPhases 1–3 on\nleft partition;
                note right
                  Breadcrumb trail
                  shows recursion
                  depth and path
                  ——
                  **Maps to:**
                  #pragma omp task
                end note
            else (base case)
                :1–2 cards →\ntrivially sorted;
            endif
        }
    fork again
        partition "Right Sub-Array" #MistyRose {
            if (Size > 1?) then (yes)
                :Sub-group repeats\nPhases 1–3 on\nright partition;
            else (base case)
                :1–2 cards →\ntrivially sorted;
            endif
        }
    end fork
}

|System|
:All sub-arrays sorted\n→ **Game complete!**;
note right
  Cards are sorted in-place.
  Task tree visualization
  shows completed recursion.
  Show completion stats.
end note
stop

legend right
  |= HPC Concept |= Game Mechanic |
  | Pivot selection | Player/system chooses pivot card |
  | Parallel partition | All players rearrange simultaneously |
  | Load imbalance | Unequal sub-arrays from bad pivot |
  | Task-based parallelism | Player sub-groups fork to sub-arrays |
  | Recursion termination | Sub-array of 1–2 cards = base case |
endlegend

center footer Players perform Parallel Quicksort using existing shared container and coordination

@enduml
